Maiharaji Altine Gusau The Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Tukur Buratai has visited Zamfara State where he had a close door discussion with Governor Bello Matawalle. Though the press were neither invited nor briefed on why the army boss was in the state, it was reliability gathered that he was in the state to condole with the families and government of the state over the killing of nine soldiers on Thursday. Copyright PUNCH.
